<TITLE> Hasina falls sick: aide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Sheikh Hasina fell sick with high blood pressure in special jail Monday, her aide said. Hasina's special assistant Hasan Mahmud said that she fell down in the bathroom at the timea claim deputy inspector general (DIG) of prisons major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui denied. Hasan Mahmud told bdnews24.com: "The leader is very sick. She had a vertigo attack around 10.30am and fell down in the bathroom." "The jail authorities tried to suppress the matter," Mahmud alleged. "Later, we came to know about it from another source around 2.30pm. I spoke to the DIG and he arranged for her personal physician to meet her." Dr Syed Modasser Ali and Dr ABM Abdullah went to the special jail in the afternoon to see Hasina. Dr Syed Modasser Ali told bdnews24.com: "We stayed there for half an hour from around 5.15pm." Asked about Hasina's physical condition, Ali said: "We won't say anything at the moment. We will speak after all tests are done." Siddiqui, DIG (prisons), told bdnews24.com, "Sheikh Hasina's blood pressure shot up and we took a doctor from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University hospital, apart from the jail doctor. But Sheikh Hasina refused to be treated by them." "Later, the personal physicians of Hasina were contacted, they came and examined her. She is now keeping well," he added. Asked why doctors were called in then, if Hasina's condition was not bad, Siddiqui did not give a direct reply but said: "That she is in good health matters." bdnews24.
